cdi is hard

that means:
	•	llm can be wrong
	•	cdi can be inspected
	•	cli can be reproduced
	•	runtime stays deterministic

⸻

3 operating modes

mode 1: suggest only

user asks
llm writes cdi preview
human reviews
human runs

best for:
	•	early stage
	•	safety
	•	debugging

⸻

mode 2: auto execute simple tasks

for trusted simple commands:

show last image
run last gen 4 more
open queue

llm can emit cdi / cli and run immediately

best for:
	•	low risk
	•	fast interaction

⸻

mode 3: hybrid

simple → auto
complex → preview first

this is probably best default

