example 3: inspect only

user:

how was this made

llm decides:
	•	no generation
	•	inspect selected artifact

cli:

beast inspect v0001234 --json

llm reformats answer for human

⸻

what llm needs to know

not whole beast internals
just:
	•	available generators
	•	cdi schema
	•	allowed fields
	•	recent artifacts
	•	current selection / context

so context pack might be:

selected artifact: v0001234
recent generator: pixel-art-pipeline
available commands: run inspect list open
allowed cdi sections: prompt model output

small
tight
local

⸻

what cli needs to support for this loop

minimum:
	•	run
	•	inspect
	•	list
	•	open
	•	--set
	•	--json

that is enough for a lot

⸻

where this breaks if designed badly

bad design 1

llm writes prose instead of cdi

problem:
	•	ambiguous
	•	hard to execute
	•	hard to reproduce

fix:
	•	require structured cdi output

⸻

bad design 2

cli has different logic than ui

problem:
	•	same intent behaves differently
	•	nightmare debugging

fix:
	•	same runtime
	•	same cdi
	•	same artifact system

⸻

bad design 3

llm directly mutates runtime state

problem:
	•	hidden magic
	•	non-reproducible

fix:
	•	everything goes through cdi / cli / artifact

⸻

strongest future flow

this is the one that matters:

voice
→ phonetic
→ beast english
→ llm interprets
→ cdi preview
→ cli run
→ artifacts appear
→ artifact click shows exact cdi lineage

that is beast becoming a full loop

⸻

marketing version

beast lets ai plan work
then executes it as a real system

or tighter:

llms suggest
beast runs
artifacts remember


